Citation.sTitle: Surface and Bulk Properties of Two Amphiphilic Phenothiazine Drugs in Different Aqueous Media
Citation.sAbstract: Surface behavior and bulk properties of two phenothiazine drugs, fluphenazine and trifluoperazine  dihydrochlorides, are reported. Surface activity studies for both amphiphilic drugs were carried out in aqueous  solutions at 20 deg C by surface tension measurements. The volumetric and compressibility properties of the  drugs were derived from density and ultrasound velocity measurements. Critical concentrations were  determined by surface tension and ultrasound data. The experiments were realized in aqueous and buffered  (pH 3.0, 5.5, and 9.2) media at 20 deg C. The buffered media were chosen below and above the different pKa s  that the drug molecules present (pKa1 and pKa2 of 3.90 and 8.10, respectively).
